'The unfortunate part, I believe, is that stuff that happens in the team room should stay there,' said Fowler.

'I thought Tom did a great job of talking to the guys. He had been there plenty of times, and I enjoyed the time I got to spend with him. I respect him, he is a legend within the game.

'Some things may have got blown a little bit out of proportion. But obviously we didn’t play as well as we needed to in order to win.'

Intriguingly, both Fowler and Mickelson are on the 11-man 'task force', which also includes Tiger Woods, appointed to end American misery in golf's biennial showpiece ahead of the next match at Hazeltine in 2016. The US have lost eight of the last 10 Ryder Cups against Europe, never got close to Paul McGinley's side in Scotland, then aired their dirty laundry in public thanks to Mickelson's comments in that now infamous press conference.

